    "view": {
      "representation": "view",
      "value": "<p>Artists can use RenderMan's Preset Browser to save and share materials, dome lights, and light rigs between DCCs and departments.</p><p>The Preset Browser works within the Solaris context and can be found under RenderMan → Preset Browser.</p><p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544640927/RenderMan_PresetManager.gif?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433083173&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544640927/RenderMan_PresetManager.gif?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433083173&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544640951\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"RenderMan_PresetManager.gif\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/gif\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544640927\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"e2343cf3-180b-4c4c-a422-71c8e180850b\" data-media-type=\"file\"></span></p><p><br/></p><hr/><h3 id=\"PresetBrowserinSolaris-LoadingHDRIs\"><strong>Loading HDRIs</strong></h3><p>Environment maps can easily be loaded into an existing domelight node by first selecting the domelight node you wish to attach the map to and selecting <em>Import and Assign to Selected</em></p><p>Choosing Import with no domelight node selected, will automatically create a domelight note and assign the selected environment map<br/><em><br/><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544640927/RenderMan_Solaris_PresetBrowser_AssignHDRI.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433082887&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544640927/RenderMan_Solaris_PresetBrowser_AssignHDRI.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433082887&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544640945\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"RenderMan_Solaris_PresetBrowser_AssignHDRI.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544640927\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"1b63516c-b6b8-4b17-8067-33bacbacd578\" data-media-type=\"file\"></span><br/><br/></em></p><hr/><h3 id=\"PresetBrowserinSolaris-LoadingMaterials\"><span style=\"font-size: 16.0px;font-weight: bold;letter-spacing: -0.006em;\">Loading Materials</span></h3><p>If you already have a Solaris Material Library node you wish to load a preset material into, simply select the <em>materiallibrary </em>node and select Import into Selected Material Library.  <br/>This will import the selected material preset into the selected Material Library.<br/><br/>If a <em>materiallibrary </em>node is not selected or does not exist, you can choose Import or Import and Assign to Selected and that preset will be loaded into a newly created Material Library<br/><br/><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544640927/RenderMan_Solaris_PresetBrowser_AssignMaterial.JPG?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433082887&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544640927/RenderMan_Solaris_PresetBrowser_AssignMaterial.JPG?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433082887&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544640942\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"RenderMan_Solaris_PresetBrowser_AssignMaterial.JPG\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544640927\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"5c8f1236-2d23-4060-a100-abfc04debed0\" data-media-type=\"file\"></span><br/><br/></p><hr/><h3 id=\"PresetBrowserinSolaris-SavingMaterials\"><span style=\"font-size: 16.0px;font-weight: bold;letter-spacing: -0.006em;\">Saving Materials </span></h3><p>Currently, there is a limitation in Solaris that will only export one material from a selected <em>materiallibrary</em>.  <br/><br/>Simply, select the <em>materiallibrary </em>node and click on the new material icon in the Preset Browser<br/><br/><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544640927/RenderMan_Solaris_SavePresets.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433082887&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544640927/RenderMan_Solaris_SavePresets.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754433082887&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544640939\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"RenderMan_Solaris_SavePresets.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544640927\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"e207a922-f26d-4b52-b9be-97f67966a95f\" data-media-type=\"file\"></span><br/><br/><br/></p><hr/><p><br/><br/></p><p><br/><br/><br/><br/></p><p><br/></p>"
    }
  },
